<subSubSection pageId="116" pageNumber="716" type="conservation">
<paragraph blockId="116.[166,1374,2699,3471]" pageId="116" pageNumber="716">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[168,517,3242,3276]" pageId="116" pageNumber="716">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
Classified as Data Deficient on The IUCN Red List. The Great Key Island Giant Rat is known only from two skins and a skull, and virtually nothing is known of the species. Further research is needed in order fully to understand its natural history, evolution, and any threats facing it.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
